<title>SWITZERLAND: Roche down on acquisition rumours.</title>
<headline>Roche down on acquisition rumours.</headline>
<dateline>ZURICH 1997-04-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares of Roche Holding AG were down 165 Swiss francs to 12,140 at 1030 GMT on speculation the company could be planning a major acquisition with proceeds of a billion dollar convertible bond, dealers said.</p>
<p>Traders said talk of an acquisition made sense because investors wanted the company to reduce its hoard of 15 billion Swiss francs in securities and liquid assets.</p>
<p>&quot;People don't want to pay high P/Es for a company that is one-third a bank,&quot; one said. Another said Roche had more than enough cash to buy Synthelabo, rumoured to be a target, without issuing a bond.</p>
<p>-- Zurich +41 1 631 7340</p>
